content.text:
{
  "decision": "revise",
  "summary": "Plan is well-structured and aligned with the stated objective: the 6x3 RPC matrix, embed-based data loader, single-server design, and ordering of slices are all sound. The verification block is concrete. However, a few foundational items are left vague (module path is a placeholder that contaminates every generated file, buf.gen.yaml is never specified, the data fetch is unpinned to a snapshot, and license/attribution for the underlying Wookieepedia-derived dataset is hand-waved). Operability gaps (no health check, no graceful shutdown, hardcoded port) and a few contract details (empty-search semantics, connect error codes) should be tightened before the first slice is executed.",
  "blockers": [
    {
      "where": "Assumptions A9 / Open questions OQ1",
      "issue": "Module path is a placeholder (github.com/example/swapi-grpc). It is baked into the go_package option, the generated imports, the go.mod, and every internal import. Replacing it later requires regenerating all proto code, rewriting every import in handlers/tests, and updating go.sum.",
      "fix": "Pick the real module path now (e.g. github.com/<owner>/swapi-grpc) and use it consistently in go.mod, proto go_package options, and the example client. If a placeholder is truly needed, scope it to a single Makefile variable that all paths expand from."
    },
    {
      "where": "S0 Bootstrap / S3 Generate",
      "issue": "buf.gen.yaml is never specified. Without an explicit plugin list (protoc-gen-go, protoc-gen-connect-go) and output strategy (local, not BSR), `buf generate` is not runnable and the gen/ tree will not appear as expected.",
      "fix": "Include the buf.gen.yaml contents in the plan (or commit it in S0). At minimum: version v2, a clean plugin block invoking protoc-gen-go and protoc-gen-connect-go with the right `out` path, and the corresponding `go install` lines."
    },
    {
      "where": "S1 Fetch & check in data / Assumption A1",
      "issue": "The plan does not pin the data to a specific swapi source snapshot or commit, and the `make data` target is undefined. swapi.info / swapi.dev data shape has historically drifted (e.g. field renames, schema additions), and there is no validation that the downloaded JSON matches the assumed schema before generation begins.",
      "fix": "Pin `make data` to a specific upstream commit or release tag, write the exact fetch command (e.g. `curl -sSL <snapshot>/people.json`), and add a programmatic schema sanity check (required fields present, expected counts) that fails the build if mismatched."
    },
    {
      "where": "License / Constraint",
      "issue": "Constraint says 'data attributed per swapi's source license' but does not name the license. The dataset is derived from Wookieepedia and is under CC-BY-SA, which has specific attribution and share-alike obligations that differ from MIT code.",
      "fix": "State the data license explicitly in the plan and add a NOTICE / DATA-LICENSE file plus an attribution section in the README listing Wookieepedia and swapi as sources."
    }
  ],
  "warnings": [
    {
      "where": "S6 Server entrypoint",
      "issue": "No graceful shutdown or signal handling is specified. Killing the server with the literal `kill $SERVER_PID` in the verification block risks dropping in-flight RPCs and looks operationally incomplete for a public-facing gRPC binary.",
      "fix": "Have cmd/server/main.go trap SIGINT/SIGTERM, call srv.Shutdown with a timeout, and drain the http.Server so the end-to-end verification can exercise the shutdown path."
    },
    {
      "where": "S6 Server entrypoint",
      "issue": "No gRPC Health v1 service. A gRPC service that exposes reflection but not health is operationally odd; load balancers and k8s probes typically expect grpc.health.v1.Health/Check.",
      "fix": "Add a Health service registration (connect-go has a generated health handler; reflection-only is not a substitute)."
    },
    {
      "where": "S6 Server entrypoint",
      "issue": "Port :8080 is hardcoded. No env var or flag to override.",
      "fix": "Use a flag (e.g. `-addr :8080`) or env var (PORT) so the binary is runnable in CI, containers, and the example client without code changes."
    },
    {
      "where": "S5 Service handlers / D1",
      "issue": "Connect error codes are not specified. A Get* RPC for an unknown ID needs connect.CodeNotFound; bad input needs connect.CodeInvalidArgument. The contract is part of the API surface.",
      "fix": "State the error mapping table (NotFound, InvalidArgument, Internal) and add tests asserting the right code is returned."
    },
    {
      "where": "S5 Service handlers / Assumption A5 / OQ3",
      "issue": "Empty search query behavior is undefined. Either 'return everything' or 'return InvalidArgument' is reasonable, but it must be specified and tested.",
      "fix": "Decide explicitly (recommend: empty query returns full list, matching List) and add a test case in S8."
    },
    {
      "where": "S6 / D4",
      "issue": "gRPC reflection is named but the package and registration call are not. With connect-go 1.18+ the correct path is connectrpc.com/grpcreflect plus a reflectv1.ReflectServer handler, not the legacy google.golang.org/grpc/reflection.",
      "fix": "List the import path and the 3-line registration block, and confirm grpcurl -plaintext localhost:8080 list works end-to-end (already in the verification, good)."
    },
    {
      "where": "S8 Handler tests",
      "issue": "All handler tests live in one service_test.go and the plan does not enumerate test cases. Minimum coverage should include: Get existing ID, Get unknown ID (NotFound), List count, Search exact match, Search substring, Search case-insensitive, Search no match, Search empty query.",
      "fix": "Split per service file (people_test.go, films_test.go, ...) and enumerate the case table in the plan."
    },
    {
      "where": "S4 Data loader",
      "issue": "The 'smoke test loaded N' is informal and not in the test suite. A future refactor could silently break JSON parsing without any CI signal.",
      "fix": "Move the count check into data_test.go as a real test (and add parse + required-field assertions)."
    }
  ],
  "nitpicks": [
    {
      "where": "S0 Bootstrap / Makefile",
      "issue": "`make help` is non-standard. Most Go projects use a default `make` target that prints a short usage banner, or just `make` with .DEFAULT_GOAL.",
      "fix": "Either drop the help target or replace with a default goal that prints usage."
    },
    {
      "where": "S0 Bootstrap / .gitignore",
      "issue": "Generated code in gen/ is gitignored. This is a project-style choice (buf pushes generated code; some projects commit it). The plan should state the choice explicitly so it does not get revisited later.",
      "fix": "Add one line to the plan: 'gen/ is gitignored; regenerated by `buf generate`.'"
    },
    {
      "where": "S3 / proto",
      "issue": "The reference proto only shows PeopleService. The other five services are implied to mirror it but their field lists are not enumerated, which makes review of FK handling (films, species, vehicles, starships, planets) impossible.",
      "fix": "Either inline all six protos in the plan or add a per-service field summary table (especially the repeated-id FK fields for cross-resource joins)."
    },
    {
      "where": "S4 Data loader",
      "issue": "`//go:embed data/*.json` requires at least one matching file at build time, otherwise the build fails. With six files expected, an empty data/ dir will break the build silently until someone runs the server.",
      "fix": "Either commit a tiny placeholder JSON (e.g. `[]`) for each resource, or add a Makefile rule that fails the build if data/*.json is empty."
    },
    {
      "where": "S6 / D5",
      "issue": "`connect.WithCORS()` with no allowed origins emits a wildcard Access-Control-Allow-Origin. For a public read-only API this is fine, but it is worth being explicit since the verification block exercises a specific Origin header.",
      "fix": "Either document 'wildcard CORS by design' or restrict to an explicit allowlist via connect.WithAllowedOrigins."
    }
  ]
}

