      "question": "The plan-reviewer flagged the module path as a blocker (it bakes into go.mod, go_package options, and all imports). How do you want to handle it?",
      "header": "Module path",
      "options": [
        {
          "label": "Use github.com/example/swapi-grpc + a rename target (Recommended)",
          "description": "Pick a sensible default now (github.com/example/swapi-grpc) and ship a `make rename-module NEW=github.com/<you>/swapi-grpc` target that does a single sed across go.mod, buf.gen.yaml, all 6 .proto files, and the example client."
        },
        {
          "label": "Use a local-only path",
          "description": "Use `swapi-grpc` (no host prefix). Works for local development but breaks the moment anyone tries to `go install` it from a VCS."
        },
        {
          "label": "I'll provide the path",
          "description": "Tell me the real org/repo now and I'll bake it into the plan and proto files."
        }
      ],
      "multiSelect": false
    },
    {
      "question": "How should the loader handle an empty `query`?",
      "header": "Empty search",
      "options": [
        {
          "label": "Empty query returns the full list (Recommended)",
          "description": "Empty `query` returns the same payload as `List` (full list, same count). Symmetric with calling List; no surprise errors."
        },
        {
          "label": "Empty query returns InvalidArgument",
          "description": "Empty `query` returns `connect.CodeInvalidArgument` (\"query must not be empty\"). Stricter, surfaces client bugs early."
        }
      ],
      "multiSelect": false
    },
    {
      "question": "What should the server do beyond the 6 services + reflection?",
      "header": "Health + config",
      "options": [
        {
          "label": "Add a gRPC Health v1 service (Recommended)",
          "description": "Register grpc.health.v1.Health/Check via the generated health handler. Standard for k8s probes / load balancers; ~5 lines in cmd/server/main.go."
        },
        {
          "label": "Configurable listen address (Recommended)",
          "description": "Add a `-addr :8080` flag (env: `PORT`) so the binary is runnable in CI/containers without code changes."
        },
        {
          "label": "Graceful SIGINT/SIGTERM shutdown (Recommended)",
          "description": "Trap SIGINT/SIGTERM, call srv.Shutdown(ctx) with a 5s grace, exit 0. Replaces the brittle `kill $SERVER_PID` in the verification block with `kill -TERM`."
        }
      ],
      "multiSelect": true
    }
  ]
}

