{
  "decision": "revise",
  "summary": "Revision 3 resolves all 5 previous blockers (data embed path, homeworld_id singular consistency, buf.gen.yaml module line, JSON-to-proto two-pass conversion via D15 intermediate structs, A9 SHA-failure claim dropped) and 6 of 7 previous warnings (D11 malformed-id test added via D19 and verified in test matrix + curl, S8 deprecated/merged into S5 with D20 keeping integration test inside the service package, D17 wires sanity test as make generate prerequisite, A3 marks luke_skywalker as illustrative, verification block exercises both SIGTERM and SIGINT, D21/S5 use .Name/.Title as fields not methods), plus all 4 previous nitpicks (no per-file $(MODULE) go_package claim, go 1.22 directive pinned in D22 and directory layout comment, case-insensitive test is TestSearch_CaseInsensitive ungated, buf.yaml has no name field per D23). One previous warning remains: the connect-go generated path in S3 and the Reference directory layout still shows per-service `<resource>v1connect/` directories (e.g., `peoplev1connect/people.connect.go`) but S5 references `swapiv1connect`, which is what connect-go 1.18+ produces by default and what the prior review explicitly requested.",
  "blockers": [],
  "warnings": [
    "S3 + Reference directory layout — shows per-service `<resource>v1connect/` (e.g. `gen/swapi/v1/swapiv1/peoplev1connect/people.connect.go`) but S5 references `swapiv1connect`; connect-go 1.18+ uses per-proto-package naming so the path should be `gen/swapi/v1/swapiv1connect/people.connect.go` — Update S3 expected paths and the Reference tree to `swapiv1connect/` for all six resources."
  ],
  "nitpicks": [
    "S0 — Makefile targets list omits `test-data` though S0 also states `make generate` depends on `make test-data` — Add `test-data` to the listed targets, or correct the dependency to `test`.",
    "D18 — states `buf.gen.yaml uses go_package_prefix with module: $(MODULE)` but the rendered buf.gen.yaml block shows a literal module string; Make variables do not expand in YAML — Either remove the `$(MODULE)` wording or clarify it is illustrative and the rename-module target rewrites the literal value."
  ]
}

